{"docId":8499,"title":"Alice Slotsky","body":"Alice Louise Slotsky (née Weisfeld) was an American historian of mathematics and Assyriologist known for her studies of Babylonian mathematics and Babylonian accounting and for her popular courses at Brown University on the Akkadian language.","categories":["20th-century American mathematicians","20th-century American women mathematicians","21st-century American mathematicians","21st-century American women mathematicians","American Assyriologists","American historians of mathematics","Articles with short description","Brown University faculty","Bryn Mawr College alumni","CS1 maint: untitled periodical","Living people","New York University alumni","Short description matches Wikidata","Use list-defined references from September 2020","Use mdy dates from September 2020","Yale University alumni","Year of birth missing (living people)"],"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alice_Slotsky"}